The paper presents a logical framework for representing and reasoning about fuzzy optimization problems, which involves the use of fuzzy answer set optimization programming. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic in computer science (cs.LO), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
